        <argsstring>(void)</argsstring>
        <name>XSecure_SlhdsaShake256sHashMsg</name>
        <param>
          <type>void</type>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>This function computes the hash of the message as required by the SLH_DSA algorithm. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><verbatim>    Gets signature and public key addresses from the instance structure for IPC
    compatibility.
</verbatim></para><para><simplesect kind="return"><para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>XST_SUCCESS if the operation was successful.</para></listitem><listitem><para>Error code otherwise. </para></listitem></itemizedlist>
</para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>For R &lt;- SIG.getR(), R = SIG[0 : n] - access from instance address</para></listitem><listitem><para>For PK.seed [0:n] and PK.root [n:2n] - access from instance address</para></listitem><listitem><para>[in] Length of public key in bytes</para></listitem><listitem><para>M&apos; &lt;- toByte(0,1) || toByte(|ctx|, 1) || ctx || M, here we send all prefix data before M</para></listitem><listitem><para>M, actual data - access from instance address </para></listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>        </inbodydescription>
